<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk.BlazorWebAssembly">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <Version>0.6.5</Version>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.5.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.5.0</FileVersion>
    <Authors>LastOnionKnight</Authors>
    <Description>Tonberry Tactics — companion web app for the in-game plugin. AskMrRobot-style hybrid gear optimizer for FFXIV. Pure-Math by default, Balance preset queued, exports plans back to the plugin via GG-PLAN:v1: strings. v0.6.5 ("Audit lit up") wires the previously-stub Meld Audit panel rows (Wrong stat / Under-tier / Overcap) to real logic against the Core priority tables and materia tier values, adds a Sell vs Replace verdict row with per-materia expandable breakdown, and syncs the vendored MateriaTiers.cs to Core v0.6.4 content (Skill Speed prefix → "Quickarm"). The audit output format deliberately mirrors the plugin's MeldAudit record shape so v0.7.x consolidation into Core won't churn this UI. Plugin v0.6.5 ships the critical HQ-offset InventoryReader fix that unlocks all of the above by including HQ-crafted gear in exports.</Description>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/TonberryTactics</RepositoryUrl>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly" Version="10.0.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.DevServer" Version="10.0.0" PrivateAssets="all" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
